docs: Creates a new contract
only the `developer` can create a new instance of this contract
use the grandma for data migration of an old contract
constructors.label: new

docs: Define the events for this contract
events.label: OrderbookEvent

docs: Get the current orderbook size
only works when the contract is `initialized`
messages.label: get_orderbook_size

docs: Retrieve a single order by ID
messages.label: get_order_by_id

docs: Update the status of an existing order.
messages.label: update_order

docs: Get all active orders for the given ticker.
messages.label: get_active_orders

docs: Count the number of active `Buy` or `Sell` orders in the order book.
messages.label: count_orders_by_side

docs: Retrieve order details based on properties such as side and status.
messages.label: get_orders_by_side

docs: get lowest sell price
messages.label: get_lowest_sell_price

docs: get highest buy price
messages.label: get_highest_buy_price

docs: Return the orders required to fill a specific buy or sell
messages.label: take_orders

docs: Scan and mark orders as expired based on their timestamps and expiration details.
This function should be called periodically to ensure that the order book is up to date, and that expired orders are removed.
messages.label: expire_orders

docs: Update the filled amount of an order after a partial trade.
this message is only callable by a upstream contract
messages.label: orderbook_management

docs: Pay the contract to create a new market
Decimals default to 6
messages.label: create_new_market

docs: Retrieves all active markets from the order book.
messages.label: get_all_markets

docs: For a given market ticker, return the market details.
Also when a market is halted
messages.label: get_market_info

docs: Retrieve `active` orders for a specific market.
messages.label: get_market_orders

docs: Retrieve `active` orders by a specific accountId.
messages.label: get_orders_by_user

docs: Purge orders.
This function allows the `admin` to remove inactive orders from the blockchain.
messages.label: purge_orders

docs: Update the status (halted/active) of a specific market.
only the `admin` can call this function
messages.label: update_market_status

docs: this call allows the admin to halt all trading
only the `admin` is allowed to call this
messages.label: halt_trading

docs: this call allows the admin to halt all trading
only the `admin` is allowed to call this
messages.label: resume_trading

docs: Terminate a market and remove its orders.
messages.label: terminate_market

docs: Update the code hash of this smart contract.
Only the `admin` is allowed to call this.
messages.label: update_contract_code_hash

docs: This call allows the admin to assign a new admin
Only the `admin` is allowed to call this
messages.label: nominate_admin

docs: This call allows the nominated admin to accept the admin role
Only the `nominated_admin` is allowed to call this
messages.label: accept_admin_role

docs: This call allows the admin to terminate the contract
Value stored in the contract will be transfered to the admin
Only the `admin` is allowed to call this
messages.label: terminate

docs: Get the contract's DID.
messages.label: contract_did
